description.narrative: WCARO provides high quality support to COs to develop effective strategies and plans for social and behaviour change aimed at increasing demand for social services and adoption of a basket of essential family practices and to prepare for and deliver humanitarian action, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNICEF Country Office programmes and humanitarian action reflect national, regional and global priorities in line with corporate strategies and guidelines
